The kookie that started it all 🍪🙌 While most people went through a sourdough phase of quarantine, I was making these babies on repeat! But baking alone just isn’t as much fun…so I called up my friend and co-creator of the Perfect 10 cookie, @christinatosi ♥️ Try them and text me how they turn out ☎️ 314-310-8545! 

Recipe deets:
1 cup slivered almonds
2/3 cup agave nectar
2/3 cup olive oil OR coconut oil
2 Tbsp vanilla extract
1 Tbsp almond butter
1 Tbsp + 1 tsp ground golden flax
2 cups gluten-free oats
2 cups almond flour
1/2 cup gluten-free, all-purpose flour
2 tspkosher salt
1/2 vegan chocolate chips

@mikaelareuben thanks for baking with me ♥️ BANANA MUFFINS RECIPE (Makes 10 muffins)

Wet :
3 medium ripe bananas (extra banana for topping)
6 tbsps maple syrup 
1/4 cup oil (olive, or avocado)
1/2 tsp vanilla extract 
Dry:
2 1/2 cups almond flour
1/2 cup arrowroot flour (tapioca starch would also work)
1/2 tsp sea salt
1 tsp baking soda
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp nutmeg
Handful of cacao nibs - or chocolate chips (vegan if ppl want vegan)

Directions 
Combine all the dry ingredients in a bowl.

In a blender, purée the wet ingredients until there are no banana chunks left. Alternatively, you can mash banana then mix into the other wet ingredients.

Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients.

Spoon into greased or lined muffin cups. 
Sprinkle muffins with cacao nibs and a slice of banana. 
Bake at 350F for 25-30 minutes, or until risen and golden.
